-- Task 2: Verify Normalisation
-- =====================================================

-- 1NF (First Normal Form)
-- All columns contain only atomic (single) values.
-- No column stores multiple values in a single field.
-- Example:
-- first_name contains only one value.
-- email contains only one email address.

-- 2NF (Second Normal Form)
-- Every non-key attribute depends on the entire primary key.
-- In the enrollments table, grade and enrollment_date
-- depend on the complete enrollment record.
-- Therefore, there are no partial dependencies.

-- 3NF (Third Normal Form)
-- There are no transitive dependencies.
-- Department details are stored only in the departments table.
-- The students table stores only department_id.
-- This avoids data redundancy and satisfies 3NF.
